29:20.860 --> 29:24.409
Hi. I called earlier from
the spiritual outreach program?

29:24.433 --> 29:26.211
Hi. Piano player, right?

29:26.235 --> 29:28.874
This is so generous of you.

29:28.898 --> 29:32.848
There it is. It's not
exactly a concert grand.

29:32.872 --> 29:35.080
I should warn you, on the whole,

29:35.104 --> 29:38.183
our patients are generally
unresponsive,

29:38.207 --> 29:41.186
so I hope you don't expect
a lot of clapping.

29:41.210 --> 29:45.130
Miss Delaney, I find when
the spiritual rewards

29:45.154 --> 29:47.893
are this great,
who needs applause?

29:47.917 --> 29:50.817
Excuse me.

30:17.917 --> 30:22.067
Did Addison talk to you
about me?

30:22.091 --> 30:24.970
Oh! I guess not.

30:24.994 --> 30:26.237
He's a married man!

30:26.261 --> 30:28.303
What's wrong with you?!
No, wait! Wait!

30:28.327 --> 30:29.835
It's not what you think!

30:29.859 --> 30:31.076
He hasn't touched me
for three years

30:31.100 --> 30:34.809
because of sluts like you!

30:34.833 --> 30:36.086
Carol, if you would just stop

30:36.110 --> 30:38.113
throwing things at me,
I'll explain!

30:38.137 --> 30:42.587
How... how can you explain?!
You're screwing my husband!

30:42.611 --> 30:45.411
No, I'm not screwing him!
He's my father!

30:48.177 --> 30:51.226
I'm so sorry.

30:51.250 --> 30:54.399
I thought you should know,
but he didn't want to tell you.

30:54.423 --> 30:57.462
I want to die.

30:57.486 --> 30:58.964
Oh, no. I do.

30:58.988 --> 31:01.336
Oh, Carol, you don't have
to clean that up.

31:01.360 --> 31:04.169
They have clerks for that.

31:04.193 --> 31:05.510
How old are you?

31:05.534 --> 31:07.512
38.

31:07.536 --> 31:12.247
We've been married 39 years.

31:12.271 --> 31:14.049
It's been going on
from the start.

31:14.073 --> 31:17.182
Believe me, I didn't want
to hurt anyone.

31:17.206 --> 31:19.955
I just wanted to find my dad.

31:19.979 --> 31:25.009
I'm glad you did,
but you be careful, sweetheart.

31:26.555 --> 31:29.655
He's gonna break your heart.

31:45.404 --> 31:47.891
Andrew, I made an appointment
with a therapist

31:47.915 --> 31:49.614
for you, me and Danielle.

31:49.638 --> 31:51.556
I don't think so.

31:51.580 --> 31:54.589
This pain that you're feeling
is completely natural,

31:54.613 --> 31:57.370
but it's not gonna go away
until you deal with it.

31:57.394 --> 32:01.066
Andrew, I want us to heal,

32:01.090 --> 32:03.198
I want us to be a family again.

32:03.222 --> 32:05.330
You know what I want?

32:05.354 --> 32:08.081
I want for George Williams
to walk through that door

32:08.105 --> 32:12.207
so I can take a knife
and plunge it into his heart.

32:12.231 --> 32:15.280
I want the pharmacist to pay
for what he did to my father.

32:15.304 --> 32:18.283
Well, the good news
is he's... He's dead.

32:18.307 --> 32:22.547
He committed suicide.
His death was on his terms.

32:22.571 --> 32:23.989
That's not justice.

32:24.013 --> 32:29.054
So are you saying
if he were executed

32:29.078 --> 32:31.926
that it would be easier
for you to get past this?

32:31.950 --> 32:33.120
Of course.

32:43.062 --> 32:49.702
George... didn't intend
to commit suicide.

32:52.671 --> 32:55.988
He was trying to manipulate me
into taking him back,

32:56.012 --> 32:59.124
and he swallowed those pills

32:59.148 --> 33:01.186
hoping that
I'd feel sorry for him.

33:01.210 --> 33:07.032
He just assumed that I would
call an ambulance.

33:07.056 --> 33:10.556
When I got there, he was
already slipping away.

33:13.092 --> 33:16.501
I tried to get him to
accept responsibility

33:16.525 --> 33:18.395
for what he'd done...

33:21.130 --> 33:22.977
But he wouldn't.

33:23.001 --> 33:25.010
So what'd you do?

33:25.034 --> 33:28.314
Nothing.

33:31.140 --> 33:35.690
I just sat there
and let him die.

33:35.714 --> 33:38.763
Oh, my god.

33:38.787 --> 33:43.498
He didn't die
on his terms, Andrew.

33:43.522 --> 33:47.262
He paid for what he did
to your father.

33:53.202 --> 33:56.742
Thank you
for telling me this.

34:25.063 --> 34:27.172
Hey, how you doin'?

35:49.618 --> 35:51.226
Yeah?

35:51.250 --> 35:52.727
Zach's come home.

35:52.751 --> 35:55.700
What? Is he okay?

35:55.724 --> 35:56.731
He's fine.

35:56.755 --> 35:58.433
Is there anything I can do?

35:58.457 --> 35:59.764
Thanks for asking.

35:59.788 --> 36:02.136
You can leave us alone.

36:02.160 --> 36:05.340
I spent a lot of time
looking for Zach,

36:05.364 --> 36:06.841
and you know why.

36:06.865 --> 36:08.343
Maybe I'm not
making myself clear.

36:08.367 --> 36:10.345
You come near my son,
I'll go to the police.

36:10.369 --> 36:13.318
I'll tell them what happened
out in that quarry.

36:13.342 --> 36:16.150
You do that
and we'll both go down.

36:16.174 --> 36:19.414
Well, you know I'm capable
of almost anything.

36:21.280 --> 36:23.258
Hey, I thought you'd like
to know

36:23.282 --> 36:25.260
Zach and I are moving away.

36:25.284 --> 36:28.268
I want to give my son
a shot at a normal life.

36:28.292 --> 36:30.195
I'm sure you'll agree
it's for the best.

36:30.219 --> 36:33.498
Now see, this is where
you and I don't see eye-to-eye.

36:33.522 --> 36:37.202
For Zach's sake,
I'll keep quiet, for now,

36:37.226 --> 36:39.404
but you're not taking him away.

36:39.428 --> 36:43.177
If I see a "for sale" sign
in front of that house,

36:43.201 --> 36:44.849
I'llcall the police.

36:44.873 --> 36:48.213
I'm capable of pretty much
anything myself.

37:03.792 --> 37:06.336
The doctor's going to
give you a full work-up,

37:06.360 --> 37:08.202
then we'll start
the inoculations.

37:08.226 --> 37:10.204
Make sure you fill out
everything

37:10.228 --> 37:12.677
and the nurse will take
you back. Thank you.

37:12.701 --> 37:15.510
Boy, sister Mary's
done a number on you.

37:15.534 --> 37:17.211
Right.

37:17.235 --> 37:18.583
Yes, right.

37:18.607 --> 37:20.415
She has you flying
halfway across the world

37:20.439 --> 37:23.688
to help the poor, and there's
perfectly good poor right here.

37:23.712 --> 37:26.296
For god's sakes, give a buck
to a homeless guy.

37:26.320 --> 37:27.322
It's not the same.

37:27.346 --> 37:29.294
No, it's better because
you can do it

37:29.318 --> 37:30.595
in the comfort of your own car.

37:30.619 --> 37:32.957
The point is not to be
comfortable, Gaby.

37:32.981 --> 37:35.400
It's about easing
pain and suffering.

37:35.424 --> 37:38.433
Look, I'm trying to be
a better person here.

37:38.457 --> 37:41.466
Now you can either help me
or you can get out of the way,

37:41.490 --> 37:43.468
but you can't stop me.

37:43.492 --> 37:46.010
Carlos solis?

37:46.034 --> 37:47.412
Come with me, please.

37:47.436 --> 37:51.276
Finish that for me.

37:55.504 --> 37:57.452
Here.

37:57.476 --> 37:59.854
He didn't fill out
the allergy section.

37:59.878 --> 38:02.887
Honey, he's going to
a remote village in Africa.

38:02.911 --> 38:05.390
Does it really matter
that he's allergic to eggs?

38:05.414 --> 38:06.801
Actually, yes.
Eggs are on the list.

38:06.825 --> 38:09.564
He could have a severe reaction
to the yellow fever vaccine,

38:09.588 --> 38:12.397
and he won't be getting out
of bed,

38:12.421 --> 38:14.469
let alone leaving the country.

38:14.493 --> 38:16.301
Really?

38:16.325 --> 38:18.473
Oh, don't write that down.

38:18.497 --> 38:22.907
I wasn't being specific.
He's allergic to fish eggs.

38:22.931 --> 38:24.479
Fish eggs?

38:24.503 --> 38:27.320
Poor baby's gone his whole life
without caviar.

38:27.344 --> 38:29.414
Now that's suffering.

38:29.438 --> 38:34.478
All right, doc, give me
all you got.

38:38.947 --> 38:41.626
It's so hot in this village.

38:41.650 --> 38:43.798
Baby, that's the fever talking.

38:43.822 --> 38:46.576
The doctor said you're having
an allergic reaction,

38:46.600 --> 38:48.503
but you're gonna be fine, okay?

38:48.527 --> 38:51.336
Hold me.

38:51.360 --> 38:56.981
Ohh, honey. I'm so sorry.

38:57.005 --> 39:00.615
Ohh, maybe that stupid nun
is right.

39:00.639 --> 39:03.918
Maybe I am trying to stop you
from becoming a better person.

39:03.942 --> 39:09.053
It's just that I love you
the way you are...

39:09.077 --> 39:12.397
Greedy, selfish and insensitive.

39:12.421 --> 39:15.329
I'm just scared if you're
not those things anymore,

39:15.353 --> 39:21.335
you're gonna wake up
one day and realize I still am,

39:21.359 --> 39:22.837
and then you won't want me.

39:22.861 --> 39:26.741
I want you. Just hold me.

39:26.765 --> 39:28.713
Ohh.

39:28.737 --> 39:32.377
Ohh, Carlos.

39:32.401 --> 39:35.480
Hold me...

39:37.375 --> 39:39.775
Sister Mary.

39:45.584 --> 39:49.934
Painting in the rain?
Is that smart?

39:49.958 --> 39:51.666
Well, let me see,
painting in the rain

39:51.690 --> 39:53.538
or letting the whole world
think I'm a whore?

39:53.562 --> 39:56.401
I don't know. What do you think?

39:56.425 --> 39:58.372
Heard you ran into my wife.

39:58.396 --> 39:59.373
Yep.

39:59.397 --> 40:01.045
So?

40:01.069 --> 40:04.579
So you are hereby released
of any further obligation

40:04.603 --> 40:06.451
to be my dad.

40:06.475 --> 40:08.583
Okay.

40:08.607 --> 40:12.917
Just so you know,
I'm not actually proud

40:12.941 --> 40:16.390
of what I've done,
you know, my hobbies.

40:16.414 --> 40:19.564
Good for you. Bye.

40:19.588 --> 40:23.568
I have done things I'm proud of.

40:23.592 --> 40:27.171
I could give you
five examples right now.

40:27.195 --> 40:29.474
Okay, maybe three.

40:29.498 --> 40:33.578
You don't have to do this.

40:33.602 --> 40:36.110
I was a volunteer fireman.

40:36.134 --> 40:39.091
I put out fires,
I got kittens out of trees,

40:39.115 --> 40:40.515
the whole nine yards.

40:40.539 --> 40:42.086
Sweet.

40:42.110 --> 40:45.189
About 20 years ago,

40:45.213 --> 40:47.827
I started a foundation
to protect wild horses.

40:47.851 --> 40:49.794
I probably saved
hundreds of them.

40:49.818 --> 40:52.657
Really?

40:52.681 --> 40:54.481
I'm full of surprises.

40:56.755 --> 40:59.664
Okay, one more.

40:59.688 --> 41:05.910
I wasn't exactly thrilled when
you walked back into my life.

41:05.934 --> 41:08.913
Now that I've met you,

41:08.937 --> 41:12.577
well, you gave me
a third thing to be proud of.

41:12.601 --> 41:16.681
That was a good one.

41:16.705 --> 41:19.505
That's why I saved it for last.

41:22.781 --> 41:25.690
I have to spend some time
working on my marriage.

41:25.714 --> 41:27.632
When that's all sorted out,

41:27.656 --> 41:32.256
maybe we could continue
with the catching up?

41:34.693 --> 41:37.633
I'll wait for your call.

41:46.675 --> 41:50.705
The stories are as old
as time itself...

41:52.280 --> 41:55.059
The prodigal son
who returns home

41:55.083 --> 41:58.023
to the father
who forgives him...

41:59.948 --> 42:03.097
The jealous wife
who tricks the husband

42:03.121 --> 42:05.091
who trusts her...

42:06.925 --> 42:11.636
The desperate mother
who risks everything

42:11.660 --> 42:14.508
for the child who needs her

42:14.532 --> 42:18.082
and the faithless husband

42:18.106 --> 42:22.647
who hurts the wife
who loves him so deeply.

42:22.671 --> 42:26.891
Why do we listen
again and again?

42:26.915 --> 42:30.054
Because these are the stories
of family,

42:30.078 --> 42:33.157
and once we look past
the fighting, pain

42:33.181 --> 42:35.730
and the resentment,

42:35.754 --> 42:40.004
we occasionally like
to remind ourselves...

42:40.028 --> 42:42.667
Hi! Hi.

42:42.691 --> 42:47.612
There is absolutely nothing
more important.

42:47.636 --> 42:49.636
Hi, bunny, bunny. Hi.
